The Kogi State House of Assembly on Tuesday confirmed the nomination of three appointees of Governor Yahaya Bello. The appointees are Abdullahi Ndalayi Suleiman, Chairman, State Universal Basic Education Board, (SUBEB), Usman Umoru, Permanent Member, (SUBEB) and Matthew Abuka, Director General, Kogi State Debt Management Office (DMO). The confirmation of the appointees is sequel to a letter sent to the house by Governor Bello extending their appointment for another tenure. Speaking to journalist shortly after he was confirmed, the Chairman, State Universal Basic Education Board, (SUBEB), Abdullahi Ndalayi Suleiman, appealed to primary school teachers to be patient with the present administration adding that, there are better days is ahead in the area of their welfare. Suleiman promised to consolidate on his first achievements by sustaining discipline, accountability and transparency. Meanwhile, a bill for a law to Establish the Kogi Signage and Advertisement Agency has passed through first reading in the Kogi State House of Assembly. The bill when passed into law will provide a legislative framework for the regulation of outdoor advertisement in the State.